KAIZER Chiefs have confirmed the appointment of former Free State Stars coach Giovani Solinas. Amakhosi chairman Kaizer Motaung has on Friday confirmed the much-anticipated appointment of a new coach via the club's official Facebook page.Solinas departed Ea Lla Koto in May 2016, citing "personal reasons" for his immediate resignation after just six months at the helm.The Italian tactician took over the Free State club from Ernst Middendorp and guided the club to 12th on the Absa Premiership standings, while also leading them to the Nedbank Cup semi-finals in 2015/16. More to follow...